    "client_msg_id": "bd452657-fd81-4182-bcbe-58ac419adb0d",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "The languages are rarely the problem (unless we go Sapir-Whorf here), but the problem is the models we express in those language and how we stick to them or not.\n\nPut differently, the problem is not that your language has Booleans, it's when you use Boolean to model gender when you create a problem.",
    "user": "U01AD80KMLK",
    "ts": "1638903303.176400",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
