  {
    "client_msg_id": "a7463987-1ba8-4943-96bc-17f721a6c0a8",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Completely agree that models are the problem. I do think I'd just add to that that what models are easy or difficult to work with and express depends on our language. \n\nSimple examples, Nats vs u32 vs integer vs floats. Some problems are better modeled with these various types. But it I'm in J's I'm probably modeling them with floats (the only real number type).\n\nHow many things do we not do or choose to not even consider because our languages make it difficult to express?",
    "user": "UK3LH8CF5",
    "ts": "1638908351.176800",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
